That's the dream.
He's right.

11:21.128 --> 11:23.228
That is the dream.
No!

11:23.230 --> 11:25.364
I refuse to look
down from the altar

11:25.366 --> 11:28.500
as I say my vowels to
the woman of my dreams,

11:28.502 --> 11:31.703
and see that
damned, stupid,

11:31.705 --> 11:33.705
accidental-curly-
fry-stealing

11:33.707 --> 11:35.674
Gary Blauman!

11:35.676 --> 11:37.008
Did you say Gary Blauman?

11:37.810 --> 11:40.078
I...

11:40.080 --> 11:41.747
hate...

11:41.749 --> 11:43.382
to disagree with Barney.

11:44.050 --> 11:45.517
But I love that guy!

11:45.519 --> 11:48.353
<i>I just met him earlier today.</i>

11:48.355 --> 11:49.821
Oh, my gosh!

11:49.823 --> 11:50.922
It's you.

11:50.924 --> 11:52.057
Yeah.

11:52.059 --> 11:54.259
You're the poet William Zabka.

11:55.762 --> 11:58.163
Nobody ever recognizes me
for my poetry.

11:58.165 --> 12:00.031
He has all six
of my collections.

12:00.933 --> 12:02.067
When Terry Gross interviewed me

12:02.069 --> 12:04.302
on <i>Fresh Air,</i> he listened live.

12:04.871 --> 12:07.272
Gary Blauman rules!

12:07.274 --> 12:08.573
Gary Blauman?

12:09.075 --> 12:11.743
I...

12:12.612 --> 12:13.745
hate...

12:14.914 --> 12:16.715
...that I once thought
I loved Gary Blauman.

12:16.717 --> 12:19.284
Ooh, this sounds good.

12:19.286 --> 12:21.920
Gary's the guy
that I had an affair with.

12:21.922 --> 12:25.690
Tom found out,
threw me out of the house.

12:25.692 --> 12:28.760
Now the kids are
from a broken home.

12:28.762 --> 12:32.297
Because of Gary Blauman,
everything that matters to me

12:32.299 --> 12:34.399
is gone.

12:37.303 --> 12:38.804
I got that beat.

12:38.806 --> 12:40.338
So, I was ordering
these fries...

12:40.340 --> 12:41.840
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

12:41.842 --> 12:42.841
Blauman's gay?

12:42.843 --> 12:43.942
Well...

12:43.944 --> 12:45.577
then that means that night,

12:45.579 --> 12:49.548
the real battle
was between Blauman

12:49.550 --> 12:51.450
and the girl.

12:51.452 --> 12:54.719
And the prize... was this guy.

12:56.089 --> 12:57.489
Keep telling yourself
that, buddy.

12:57.491 --> 12:59.191
I don't want to see Gary Blauman
at my brother's wedding.

12:59.193 --> 13:00.311
Neither do I!

13:00.336 --> 13:01.427
I'm the brother in question!
Now, now, hold on.

13:04.331 --> 13:06.465
Order! Order!

13:06.467 --> 13:09.434
Robin put this on my plate,
and so I'll make the decision.

13:09.436 --> 13:12.003
Now, let's take a short recess.

13:12.005 --> 13:12.971
Everybody out.

13:12.973 --> 13:14.439
Okay.

13:14.441 --> 13:17.342
Lily, out of court settlement.

13:17.344 --> 13:20.045
Drop this whole thing,
and I'll give you ten bucks.

13:20.047 --> 13:21.947
No.

13:24.317 --> 13:26.518
I can't go higher than ten.

13:28.789 --> 13:32.624
I'm ready to give
my decision.

13:32.626 --> 13:33.725
This was a tough one.

13:33.727 --> 13:35.527
Lot of good points
on both sides.

13:35.529 --> 13:38.396
But ultimately... Blauman stays.

13:38.398 --> 13:39.464
Yeah.
What in the...?

13:39.466 --> 13:40.799
For one simple reason.

13:40.801 --> 13:43.935
There is a higher law
at every wedding.

13:43.937 --> 13:46.471
A law that trumps
all other arguments.

13:46.473 --> 13:49.841
When the bride asks
for something, she gets it.

13:49.843 --> 13:50.709
Yes.

13:50.711 --> 13:52.210
- Wow.
- Good point.

13:52.212 --> 13:53.378
He's right.

13:53.380 --> 13:55.780
This fake court thing
is adjourned.

13:55.782 --> 13:58.717
Judged.

13:58.719 --> 14:00.485
Well, I guess
let's go find Blauman

14:00.487 --> 14:01.887
and tell him the good news.

14:01.889 --> 14:03.588
Yeah, about that.
Bit of a wrinkle.

14:03.590 --> 14:05.924
I was just in the hallway,
ran into Blauman.

14:05.926 --> 14:07.859
I told him
if he didn't leave immediately,

14:07.861 --> 14:09.995
then Billy Zabka was gonna
crane-kick him in the face.

14:09.997 --> 14:11.096
What?!

14:11.098 --> 14:12.731
But that's not
even my move!

14:12.733 --> 14:13.598
I...

14:13.600 --> 14:14.533
We have to stop him.

14:14.535 --> 14:15.901
Barney!
I...

14:15.903 --> 14:17.669
Come on, come on, come on.

14:17.671 --> 14:19.170
So, we all run out
to the parking lot

14:19.172 --> 14:21.740
to stop Gary Blauman from
leaving the wedding...

14:22.675 --> 14:24.442
What are you doing?

14:24.444 --> 14:25.844
This is my place.

14:25.846 --> 14:28.480
Oh.

14:28.482 --> 14:29.948
So, uh...

14:29.950 --> 14:33.151
well, I guess this...
this is where I leave you.

14:37.589 --> 14:39.557
This is your place.

14:39.559 --> 14:41.326
Yup.

14:41.328 --> 14:44.262
You sure it's not
a few blocks that way?

14:44.264 --> 14:46.664
Nope, it's right here.

14:46.666 --> 14:48.933
It's right
where you picked me up.

14:48.935 --> 14:50.601
So it is.

14:52.404 --> 14:55.740
Well... good night.

14:55.742 --> 14:56.774
Good night.

14:58.243 --> 14:59.978
<i>Eight years earlier,</i>
<i>I probably would've given</i>

14:59.980 --> 15:01.546
<i>some embarrassing speech,</i>
<i>confessed my love</i>

15:01.548 --> 15:02.780
<i>and scared her off.</i>

15:02.782 --> 15:04.282
<i>But I didn't.</i>

15:04.284 --> 15:07.251
<i>Because somehow I just knew</i>
<i>this was all gonna work out.</i>

15:07.253 --> 15:09.087
Ted?
Oh, thank God.

15:13.759 --> 15:16.627
Do you at least want
to finish your story?

15:16.629 --> 15:19.731
Right.

15:19.733 --> 15:23.034
So, we all ran out
to the parking lot, and...

15:23.036 --> 15:25.269
Blauman, Blauman,
I'm sorry.

15:25.271 --> 15:27.372
You can stay. Billy won't
kick you in the face.

15:27.374 --> 15:28.673
It's not even my move.

15:28.675 --> 15:30.675
If I was gonna do anything,
I'd sweep the leg,

15:30.677 --> 15:32.877
and put you in a body bag;
everyone knows that.

15:32.879 --> 15:35.480
What...?
Is that from one of your poems?

15:35.482 --> 15:37.248
Thank you for that.

15:38.217 --> 15:40.084
Please stick around,
for the bride.

15:40.086 --> 15:42.453
You're not a Taft.
Even if you are,

15:42.455 --> 15:44.022
Roosevelt shouldn't have
divided the party like that.

15:44.024 --> 15:45.656
I mean, he handed the
election to Wilson.

15:45.658 --> 15:47.325
Completely, right?
Right? Right?

15:48.395 --> 15:50.395
No, wait! No! All right?

15:50.397 --> 15:51.629
Forget it!

15:52.498 --> 15:54.298
And, James, I'm sorry

15:54.300 --> 15:55.533
about you and Tom.

15:55.535 --> 15:58.236
But you have to stop blaming me
for your own decisions.

15:59.138 --> 16:01.773
Well, guys, take a good look.

16:01.775 --> 16:05.209
This face you won't
be seeing again.

16:06.912 --> 16:09.781
Come...

16:09.783 --> 16:11.049
The bri... the bri...

16:11.051 --> 16:13.551
Gary?

16:15.154 --> 16:16.854
He's really leaving.

16:16.856 --> 16:18.156
Hey, Barney.

16:18.957 --> 16:20.825
You still, uh,
have my wedding ring?

16:20.827 --> 16:23.261
Yeah.

16:24.563 --> 16:26.697
I've got some work to do.

16:26.699 --> 16:28.933
Excuse me.

16:31.737 --> 16:33.104
Blauman will cool off
eventually.

16:33.106 --> 16:34.272
We'll see him again.

16:34.274 --> 16:35.139
Of course we will.

16:35.141 --> 16:36.407
I don't know.

16:36.409 --> 16:38.810
I mean, we might
really never see him again.

16:38.812 --> 16:41.079
Because I remember
at our wedding

16:41.081 --> 16:42.480
looking out and thinking,

16:42.482 --> 16:44.849
"Man, everyone here means
so much to me."

16:45.584 --> 16:46.884
A bunch of those people,

16:46.886 --> 16:49.320
you know,
I haven't seen them since.

16:49.322 --> 16:51.289
<i>And that's how it goes, kids.</i>

16:51.291 --> 16:54.158
<i>The friends, neighbors,</i>
<i>drinking buddies</i>

16:54.160 --> 16:56.160
<i>and partners in crime</i>
<i>you love so much</i>

16:56.162 --> 16:58.996
<i>when you're young,</i>
<i>as the years go by,</i>

16:58.998 --> 17:00.865
<i>you just lose touch.</i>

17:03.168 --> 17:04.535
<i>That being said,</i>

17:04.537 --> 17:07.438
<i>I did manage to keep track</i>
<i>of a few people.</i>

17:07.440 --> 17:10.608
<i>Carl's still behind the bar</i>
<i>at MacLaren's.</i>

17:10.609 --> 17:12.477
Hey, watch it over there.

17:12.479 --> 17:13.978
Yeah, watch it over there!

17:13.980 --> 17:15.880
It's become a family business.

17:15.882 --> 17:17.748
<i>Jeanette was arrested</i>
<i>for mailing jars of urine</i>

17:17.750 --> 17:18.983
<i>to Val Kilmer.</i>

17:18.984 --> 17:20.117
<i>No, not that Val Kilmer.</i>

17:20.119 --> 17:21.986
<i>She narrowly avoided</i>
<i>prison time,</i>

17:21.988 --> 17:25.189
<i>but did receive mandatory</i>
<i>psychological counseling.</i>

17:25.191 --> 17:27.959
Hello, handsome.

17:27.961 --> 17:31.195
I should say up front, I'm
not allowed to date my...

17:31.197 --> 17:32.363
Oh, what the hell.

17:32.365 --> 17:35.733
<i>She and Kevin live</i>
<i>in Poughkeepsie now.</i>

17:35.735 --> 17:38.669
<i>Ranjit made a couple really</i>
<i>good stock picks, and, well,</i>

17:38.671 --> 17:40.538
<i>he owns the limo service now.</i>

17:40.540 --> 17:42.540
Bitterman, get the car.

17:42.542 --> 17:44.242
Getting the car, sir.

17:44.244 --> 17:46.677
<i>Patrice has</i>
<i>her own drive-time radio show.</i>

17:46.679 --> 17:48.446
<i>People call in,</i>
<i>she gives advice.</i>

17:48.448 --> 17:50.615
Because
sometimes I just feel like

17:50.617 --> 17:52.083
he never listens to me,
you know?

17:52.085 --> 17:54.252
Gosh, caller,
that's a real pickle.

17:54.254 --> 17:56.087
You know,
my grandma always says...

17:56.089 --> 17:58.256
Damn it, Patrice,
I'm not finished!

17:58.258 --> 18:00.525
Sorry, sorry, go on.

18:00.527 --> 18:02.627
<i>William Zabka became</i>
<i>the youngest poet ever</i>

18:02.629 --> 18:05.530
to win the American Humanities
<i>Medal for Literature.</i>

18:05.532 --> 18:08.833
<i>He's currently working on</i>
<i>a collection of travel essays.</i>

18:08.835 --> 18:10.401
Hyah!

18:10.403 --> 18:12.603
<i>Zoey pops up in the news</i>
<i>every now and then</i>

18:12.605 --> 18:14.839
<i>supporting some cause</i>
<i>or another.</i>

18:14.841 --> 18:16.641
<i>It doesn't always</i>
<i>go well for her.</i>

18:16.643 --> 18:18.009
The hawk is a majestic creature!

18:18.011 --> 18:19.677
She means you no har...

18:19.679 --> 18:22.280
Aah, no! I'm your friend!
I'm helping you!

18:22.282 --> 18:24.182
<i>Still, it's nice knowing</i>
<i>she's out there</i>

18:24.184 --> 18:25.750
<i>fighting the good fight.</i>

18:25.752 --> 18:27.185
<i>Scooter's been married</i>
<i>for a while.</i>

18:27.187 --> 18:28.920
<i>Apparently, he met</i>
<i>a girl at work,</i>

18:28.922 --> 18:30.488
and it was love at first sight.

18:30.490 --> 18:33.391
<i>I guess something about her</i>
<i>helped him get over Lily.</i>

18:33.393 --> 18:35.459
You look beautiful today,
Jasmine.

18:35.461 --> 18:37.295
Like every day.

18:37.297 --> 18:39.964
Move. I serve
sloppy joe now.

18:39.966 --> 18:42.567
Blitz struggled with a gambling
<i>addiction for a while.</i>

18:42.569 --> 18:45.603
<i>But after a three-day bender</i>
<i>on the same slot machine,</i>

18:45.605 --> 18:46.704
<i>he finally kicked it.</i>

18:46.706 --> 18:48.906
I got to get help.

18:53.812 --> 18:56.714
Yes!

18:56.716 --> 18:58.549
Aw, man!

18:58.551 --> 19:00.651
<i>I'm not sure what happened</i>
<i>to Blah Blah.</i>

19:00.653 --> 19:03.020
<i>But I'd like to think</i>
<i>that wherever she is, she...</i>

19:03.022 --> 19:05.756
<i>Carol! Her name was Carol!</i>

19:05.758 --> 19:07.158
Thank you.

19:07.160 --> 19:08.793
<i>Sandy Rivers' inappropriate</i>
<i>office behavior</i>

19:08.795 --> 19:11.762
<i>finally caught up with him,</i>
<i>ending his news career...</i>

19:11.764 --> 19:13.297
<i>in America.</i>

19:25.811 --> 19:27.411
<i>He hasn't changed.</i>

19:27.413 --> 19:30.047
<i>It took some doing,</i>
<i>but James finally convinced Tom</i>

19:30.049 --> 19:32.049
<i>to take him back.</i>

19:32.051 --> 19:35.953
<i>And nobody's happier about it</i>
<i>than their kids.</i>

19:35.955 --> 19:40.524
Hey, kids, have I ever told you
how I met your father?

19:40.526 --> 19:42.026
It was at a party.

19:42.028 --> 19:44.962
<i>And as for Blauman...</i>

19:47.232 --> 19:48.766
Guys, wait!

19:50.003 --> 19:51.469
I'm sorry for storming off
like that.

19:51.471 --> 19:53.170
I don't want to miss
this wedding.

19:53.172 --> 19:55.306
<i>You will be shocked, kids,</i>

19:55.308 --> 19:57.308
<i>when you discover</i>
<i>how easy it is in life</i>

19:57.310 --> 19:59.543
<i>to part ways</i>
<i>with people forever.</i>

19:59.545 --> 20:02.446
<i>That's why</i>
<i>when you find someone</i>

20:02.448 --> 20:06.617
<i>you want to keep around,</i>
<i>you do something about it.</i>

20:06.619 --> 20:09.120
So, I guess...

20:09.122 --> 20:10.721
good night.

20:11.957 --> 20:14.892
Good night.

20:31.810 --> 20:33.611
Unless...

20:33.613 --> 20:35.713
do you want
to walk around some more?

20:35.715 --> 20:37.248
It's still early.

20:38.550 --> 20:41.185
Sure.

20:46.358 --> 20:48.592
What are you doing?

20:51.229 --> 20:53.397
Remembering this.

20:54.966 --> 20:56.233
Come on.

